FBIS4-1436 "drafr082_cs94029" FBIS-AFR-94-082-S Daily Report 27 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Viljoen Casts Vote, Urges End to Bomb Campaign Viljoen Casts Vote, Urges End to Bomb Campaign MB2704091894 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0904 GMT 27 Apr 94 MB2704091894 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Report by E. van Wyk] [Text] Pretoria April 27 SAPA -- Freedom Front leader Constand Viljoen was accompanied by a large group of former police and defence force generals when he cast his vote for his party at the Voortrekkerhoogte Town Hall on Wednesday [27 April]. Gen Viljoen told the media that he condemned the Jan Smuts Airport bomb blast and urged those responsible to stop the bombings and rather vote for the Freedom Front to strengthen the party's hand in future negotiations. Gen Viljoen described his voting in the country's first ever democratic election as the "last possible peaceful way to achieve the goal of self-determination".
